The President has also lined up goodies for MCAs, youth and women groups to reach out to the key blocks who will make or break the referendum. MCAs got the first bite of the cherry last week when they were promised Sh2m car grants. President gives directive that all stalled development projects be completed expeditiously. DP’s allies dismiss Koinange’s comments as “the last kicks of a dying horse”. The Constitution provides that every political party shall have a national character. Former Agriculture CS tells President to reveal why he sacked him. Kiambu court to make ruling on his bail application on Thursday.